verbose_text: Increased abilities of motility and invasiveness are linked to enhanced local growth of tumor cells, decreased cell-cell adhesion as well as degradation of basement membranes and stroma, referred to as EMT, a frequently observed phenotypic change usually caused by oncogenes, and by degradation of the basement membranes initiated by increased matrix metalloproteinases and collagenases.
